com.facebook.concurrency

Class UnstoppableExecutorServiceFront

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.concurrency.UnstoppableExecutorService
      • com.facebook.concurrency.UnstoppableExecutorServiceFront
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Executor, ExecutorService

    public class UnstoppableExecutorServiceFront
extends UnstoppableExecutorService
    combines the functionality of an ExecutorServiceFront and UnstoppableExecutorService. The net effect is a virtual executor over another. You bound the number of 'virtual threads' (Drainers) and optionally a max time slice each Drainer may use. This is approximate as a Drainer does not interrupt tasks running--it only checks between tasks to see if the maxTimeSlice is reached and then gives up the underlying thread in the delegate executor

        public UnstoppableExecutorServiceFront(BlockingQueue<Runnable> workQueue,
                               ExecutorService executor,
                               String poolName,
                               int maxDrainers,
                               long maxTimeSlice,
                               TimeUnit maxTimeSliceUnit)
        Parameters:
        workQueue - queue to use for storing tasks before executing
        executor - delegate executor to submit virtual threads to (Drainers)
        poolName - used to name the thread while being used
        maxDrainers - number of virtual threads
        maxTimeSlice - after every task, a drainer will check and see if the maxTimeSlice has passed and will terminate, but re-submit itself into the executor ('fair-share' the underlying executor)
        maxTimeSliceUnit - units for above
